data.title: Great Local Dining!
data.text: We live in town, and love to go here.  Their coffee drinks are the best, and we have become great fans of their breakfasts.  They give large portions of delicious food, and the atmosphere is perfect for us.  Make sure you stop by when you are in town!

data.title: place to meet a friend
data.text: I've been here several times meeting different friends. Each meal I've had has been good. Nothing special though.

data.title: Great little lunch stop off
data.text: Wanted a good sandwich so decide to try this one . Should of come a long time ago. I had a turkey bacon wrap with cheese wife had a "grown up" grilled cheese. Quick service excellent food and service. On the west end of Main Street.

data.title: Feels like a good neighborhood coffee shop.
data.text:
I haven't yet eaten here, although friends I was with did, and they liked their food. I've just been in to have tea with friends and family, and it reminds me a bit of the cafe where "Friends" always met.

They have a nice selection of teas and coffees, and a sandwich menu, and desserts that looked really tempting, even to a person who was not ready to eat.

There is a comfortable seating area, as well as typical tables and chairs, some local decor, and an almost cafeteria-style atmosphere. They have a station where guests get their own ice water, and you order and pick up your food at the counter.

It can get quite loud inside. I wouldn't recommend it for business meetings or book club. 

The staff behind the counter were friendly enough, but they weren't super swift to bus tables - my mom had to wipe off the table we chose to use.

I want to give this more than three stars (average) rating, but I really can't until I try the food myself and see.

data.title: Excellent salad!
data.text: I really like this place. It's comfy if you wish to eat in and it's quick if you wish to carry out. I had one of their salads and found it filling and tasty. The baked goods looked great but I did not indulge. The staff are friendly and the ambience is that of a college town hang out. Loved it!

owner_response.author: Marilou H, Manager at The Washburne Cafe, responded to this review
owner_response.text: We are so glad you enjoyed your salad and hope to see you again soon.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Good food slow service
data.text: Cute cafe , nice food but the service is a bit slow . It is small but still very nice . The parking is not easy and that is probably the reason why I will not come here again

data.title: A Wonderful Spot Anytime
data.text: This is mostly a meet, visit and enjoy shop.  However, not only can you get breakfast, lunch, specialty coffee drinks and wonderful desserts, you can also pick up a fast gift.  Their chicken salad is my favorite.

data.title: Have never been disappointed
data.text: Love this quiet quaint historic spot in downtown Springfield.  Great food, nice people and lingering over a conversation or cup of coffee is ok.

data.title: Don't tell anyone about my favorite meeting place!
data.text: There's just enough room here in this historic building for you, me, and the rest of us that already LOVE this nostalgic coffee house. 😄. The food, drinks, and service are all great!  The staff knows how to make things just right. But if the word gets out, we might have to end up waiting in line for a seat. 😉

owner_response.author: Marilou H, Owner at The Washburne Cafe, responded to this review
owner_response.text: We are so glad you enjoy The Washburne Café!  Don't worry not everyone has found it yet, we have plenty of room.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: Springfield surprise
data.text: A friend of mine suggested we go to this cafe. I don't drink coffee and typically just avoid cafés but I decided to just go and get a tea. We ended up ordering food which we both were very happy with. It was a great place to catch up with a friend. I'm sure we will be back.

data.title: Quaint and quiet
data.text: If you are looking for a nice place to just sit and relax this is the place. There were quite a few people here when we arrived and none were in a hurry to exit. My daughter loved being able to drink tea and read without being hurried. Staff are friendly and attentive but not hovering or intrusive. Nice menu, decent prices. Will become a regular watering hole for our family.

data.title: HIdden Gem in Downtown Springfield
data.text:
I was surprised to see such a happening place on a Tuesday morning!  Great service, great ambiance, and decent food!
I noticed a group of ladies, about 8-10, were meeting for a study.  It was nice to see a place accommodate this.
I wished I had more time to browse the goods that were available for purchase.

Will definately  be going back

data.title: Great place for breakfast
data.text: Breakfast on two occasions - great food both times. Very nice menu selection. Food was prepared quickly. Staff are most pleasant.

data.title: Great for breakfast
data.text: A large group of birders showed up in late morning and were promptly seated.  Food was abundant, done right.  Wait staff was quick, witty and efficient.  Coffee was fine.  When someone asked for something special, it appeared fast and with a smile.  Good prices, funky fun decor, friendly casual atmosphere.

data.title: Nice cafe delivers good coffee and food, not a greasy spoon.
data.text: We were traveling from Seattle to San Francisco and stayed overnight in one of the many innocuous motels in Springfield.  Who knew they had an adorable downtown?!  The Washburne was the perfect spot to grab espresso, and an omelet for breakfast.  This is not a restaurant with traditional table service, more like a café...you order at the counter then take your number to your table, where your meal is delivered.  The ambience was nice, the portions were perfect...not mountains of food, but delicious toast/potatoes came with my omelet.  Nice spot, and great jumping off point for exploring the many antique shops downtown!

owner_response.author: Marilou H, Owner at The Washburne Cafe, responded to this review
owner_response.text: Thank you so much for stopping in.  Hope to see you next time you're passing through our area.
owner_response.title: Owner Response

data.title: A little gem of a place!
data.text: It's located in the old Springfield Armory Building, downtown Springfield. Very quaint and has the feel of yesterday. The menu has breakfast and lunch items, coffees & teas, panini sandwiches, salads  (I love the Greek), desserts and wine & beer. The staff is friendly, knowledgeable and make you want to come back really soon. Great place for breakfast or lunch or just to stop in for a glass of wine.

data.title: Breakfast
data.text:
The breakfast menu has many delicious items.  My husband and I were both pleased with our choices.  Bakery is made on sight and looked terrific.   The gal taking our order was friendly and helpful.
Then it is brought to the table.  The restaurant is cute and was a fun place for us to stop.

data.title: Best Coffee in Town
data.text:
Great place for delicious coffee and great food items with that home cooked taste! Everything Ive tried on the breakfast menu was very tasty! Ive given up on the hassle
of trying to get a good cup of coffee in Eugene, but here its relaxing and fast service, and friendly barristas.

data.title: Poor Quality
data.text: Although the white mocha I ordered was absolutely delicious, the food was not. The lady who took my order made it to go when I had clearly stated that it was not. Whilst eating, there was tiny bugs and spiders crawling all over the table which made it hard to enjoy the meal. From all of the rave reviews I had heard, the service and food didn't live to expectations. The portions are ridiculously small but more expensive than other cafés. Definitely going to be sticking to Starbucks.

data.title: Mother's Day with 12 others
data.text: The staff was sweet and they took our reservations on the holiday! The food was good but the portions were ridiculously small! 3 of the 4 men left hungry the 4th had to order an entire second meal!! Could not get a double biscuits and gravy without paying for a whole 2nd meal!!  When we got home 1/2 hour after the meal we had to feed the kids right away!!
